'''Central Connecticut State University''' is a state university in [[New Britain, Connecticut|New Britain]], [[Connecticut]], [[United States]]. The school was moved to its present campus in 1922. The school's slogan is "Start with a dream, finish with a future."
==History== 1849: Founded as New Britain Normal School to train teachers (6th normal school in US)<ref>Fowler 1949, p. 22.</ref> 1867â69: Closed due to opposition in [[Connecticut General Assembly]].<ref>Fowler 1949, p. 59.</ref> 1920s: States begin four year education degrees. 1930: State Board of Education extends normal school curriculum from two to three years 1933: General Assembly creates Teachers College of Connecticut. Last two-year diplomas granted 1934: First bachelor's degrees granted to 61 students<ref>Fowler 1949, p. 84.</ref> 1935: Last three-year diploma awarded 1959: Renamed Central Connecticut State College. 1983: Renamed Central Connecticut State University
